"n.群岛 【英】 n. 群岛(a group or chain of many islands) 【考】 range : mountain / chain : link / archipelago : island(山组成山脉/链环成 链条/岛屿组成群岛) 【记】 archi(多)+pelago(海 )→海中的东西→群岛 n. 群岛 【记】1)archi主要的, 多, pelago海－海中有很多岛－群岛2)archi主要的, pelago读: 怕路过. 主要怕路过. 在大海中航行, 主要的怕路过的地方不就是群岛吗, 因为那里暗礁太多. 3)中间有chip(n 碎片): 群岛就是象碎片一样散落在海中的! 4)arch弧形, ipelago, 群岛一般是弧形的 【类】range: mountain = chain: link = archipelago: island(不确定)山脉由山组成 = 链条由链环组成 = 群岛由岛屿组成glade: wood = oasis: desert = archipelago: ocean 林间空地对树木 = 绿洲对沙漠 = 群岛对海洋grove: trees = archipelago: islands = galaxy: stars小树林由树木组成 = 群岛由岛屿组成 = 星系由星星组成 【注】不确定的选项, 有可能是迷惑选项或者少了一层对应关系, 但也有可能是对的. 以后用『』表示. 【记】音：爱琴 + pelag-海→爱琴海群岛；ark 诺亚方舟 + go 经过→经过海上群岛 【相关】pelagic(海的) archipelago (n.)  c.1500, from Italian arcipelago ""the Aegean Sea"" (13c.), from Greek arkhipelagos, from arkhi- ""chief"" (see archon) + pelagos ""sea"" (see pelagic). The Aegean Sea being full of island chains, the meaning was extended in Italian to ""any sea studded with islands."" Klein, noting the absence of arkhipelagos in ancient or Medieval Greek (the modern word in Greek is borrowed from Italian) believe it is an Italian mistake for Aigaion pelagos ""Aegean Sea"" (Medieval Latin Egeopelagus), or influenced by that name."
